title: Port Melbourne Man Jailed For Violent Stabbing Attack On Owner Of Local Tobacconist | 10 News
description: A Port Melbourne man who unleashed a violent stabbing attack on the owner of a local tobacconist has been jailed. The 49-year-old says he has no memory of his actions, but his victim suffered lifelong injuries, the judge saying it was sheer luck the grandmother was not killed. title: Putin Breaks Silence On Peace Negotiations And Demands Ukraine Hand Over Territory | 10 News
description: Vladimir Putin has broken his silence on peace negotiations, doubling down on his demands for Ukraine to give up territory. Speaking to reporters during a trip to Kyrgyzstan, the Russian President said there can be no agreement to lay down arms without Ukraine surrendering the territory it has already lost and agreeing to elections. title: Aussies Forecast To Spend $804 Each During Black Friday Sales | 10 News+

title: Retired Nationals Senator John 'Wacka' Williams Reacts To Barnaby Joyce’s Departure | 10 News+
description: After Barnaby Joyce’s departure from the Nationals and sandwich-pressed steak dinner with Pauline Hanson, suggesting he might be bound for One Nation, his former colleagues have been giving mixed responses. Senator Bridget McKenzie claimed any siding with Pauline Hanson would be an act of betrayal, while Matt Canavan wants Joyce back in the fold. Joining 10 News+ is retired Nationals Senator and party elder John 'Wacka' Williams to give his thoughts.
